    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-10T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-10T06:00:00-05:00" n="508"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/11872: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-10T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 10, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegrams of June 6, 4 p.m. and June 9, 10 p.m. [<hi
                        rend="italic">a.m.</hi>], the Governor General of the Belgian Congo<note
                        n="46a" xml:id="d508fn46a">Pierre M. J. Ryckmans.</note> has asked me <pb
                        facs="0585" n="573" xml:id="pg_573"/> to inform the Department that an
                    attack from the North on the line of support to Egypt through Matadi,
                    Leopoldville and Stanleyville could not be successfully defended with [<hi
                        rend="italic">without?</hi>] more military equipment. He asks that this be
                    given full consideration in passing on orders for military supplies now being
                    placed through the Belgian Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
